provide an option for over provisioning of services

Users generally don't use 100% of their quota.  This
is an initial implementation of over provisioning
support.  For now, it is binary.  In the future,
we might add a feature that sets the max allowable
over provisioning amount, likely expressed
as a % of the committed capacity.

(cherry pick of anfernee/vcap-services b731d2cdac78a78d10ef
with minor edits, including disallowing over provisioning
by default)

use standard PATH for finding mysql bins

we shouldn't make assumptions in the default configs as to
where various binaries live, doing so messes up devs
running unit tests, especially if they are on a mac
and use macports/fink/homebrew etc.
cleanup connections in the mysql unit tests

use localhost instead of 127.0.0.1 for mysql mgmt

while you might think that these would be the same,
they are not.  you have to use localhost if you
want to connect over the unix domain socket.
(This is a mysql quirk, not vcap)
log mysql connection errors as errors not info
use logger in the correct scope in mongo backup
